{"legislative_session": "2026", "identifier": "SB 91", "title": "Syringe exchange program.", "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": ["bill"], "subject": ["ADDICTION SERVICES; Illicit Drugs, Prescription Drugs, Substances, and Alcohol", "AGENCIES; Department of Health (IDOH)", "CRIMINAL LAW AND PROCEDURE; Illicit Drugs, Substances, and Alcohol Offenses", "HEALTH; Communicable Diseases, Infectious Diseases", "HEALTH; Generally", "HEALTH; Prescription Drugs and Medications"], "abstracts": [{"note": "Digest", "abstract": "Prohibits a qualified entity that operates a syringe exchange program (program) from establishing or operating a fixed site for the distribution or exchange of a syringe or needle within 1,000 feet of specified facilities. Creates an exception. Allows the Indiana department of health to deny, suspend, or revoke a qualified entity's annual registration for a violation. Amends the duties of a qualified entity that operates a program. Establishes requirements for program participation. Prohibits a qualified entity that operates a program from providing chemical reagents or precursors. Requires the state health commissioner to investigate any complaint regarding a qualified entity's noncompliance with the qualified entity's duties concerning the operation of a program. Permits the state health commissioner to suspend or terminate the approval of a qualified entity for noncompliance. Extends the expiration of the program to July 1, 2031."}], "other_titles": [], "other_identifiers": [{"identifier": "ocd-bill-in-2026-sb91"}], "actions": [{"description": "First reading: referred to Committee on Health and Provider Services", "date": "2025-12-09", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": ["reading-1", "referral-committee"], "related_entities": [{"name": "Health and Provider Services", "entity_type": "organization", "organization_id": null}]}, {"description": "Authored by Senator Crider", "date"